      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180&deg;C/ 160&deg;C (fan)/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 4</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>kale</strong> to a baking tray, sprinkle with the <strong>s</strong><strong>esame seeds</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 12-15 min or until crunchy - this is your <strong>crispy kale</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
